8 SECTION 6. TEMPORARY PROVISION--STUDY AND REPORT
9 REQUIRED.--
10 A. The legislative education study committee, in
11 collaboration with the legislative finance committee, the
12 public school insurance authority, the Albuquerque public
13 school district, the public education department and the
14 health care authority, shall conduct a comprehensive study
15 and produce a final report regarding the sustainability of
16 insurance programs for public school employees.
17 B. The study required pursuant to this section
18 shall evaluate the anticipated future needs of public school
employee insurance programs, including assessing:
19
(1) the impacts of combining public school
20
employee insurance programs with other existing public group
21
health insurance programs;
22
(2) the necessary agency actions required to
23
integrate the group health insurance and alternative plans of
24
the public school insurance authority, the health care
25 HAFC/HB 47
Page 13

1 authority and the Albuquerque public school district by June
2 30, 2029; and
3 (3) the necessary legislative action
4 required during the 2027 legislative session to integrate the
5 group health insurance and alternative plans of the public
6 school insurance authority, the health care authority and the
7 Albuquerque public school district by June 30, 2029.
8 C. The final report required pursuant to this
9 section shall be completed no later than October 1, 2026 and
10 shall be provided to the governor, the legislative finance
11 committee and the public education department.
12 SECTION 7. EFFECTIVE DATE.--
13 A. The effective date of the provisions of
14 Sections 1 and 4 through 6 of this act is July 1, 2026.
15 B. The effective date of the provision of Sections
16 2 and 3 of this act is July 1, 2027. HAFC/HB 47
